📌 Abstract

Deep learning models for cancer detection often behave as black-box systems, providing predictions without insight into the underlying decision-making process.

This research proposes a Hybrid Classical–Quantum Neural Network (HQNN) framework that integrates:

DenseNet121 for classical feature extraction

Variational Quantum Circuits (VQCs) for quantum feature processing

Noise simulation to evaluate robustness on NISQ-era quantum hardware

The system investigates whether quantum circuits can learn interpretable diagnostic features from mammography images while maintaining performance under realistic quantum noise.

🧠 Research Objectives

This project aims to:

• Explore quantum-enhanced feature learning for medical imaging
• Evaluate quantum circuit interpretability
• Study noise robustness in NISQ devices
• Compare multiple quantum neural network architectures

