🔬 Quantum Neural Network Architectures

Three quantum circuit configurations are implemented to analyze the contribution of quantum components.

1️⃣ Single-Qubit Rotation Model

Configuration

Parameter	Value
Qubits	1
Gates	RX, RY, RZ
Entanglement	None

Purpose

Evaluate the performance of minimal quantum representation.

2️⃣ Entanglement-Only Model

Configuration

Parameter	Value
Qubits	4
Gates	Hadamard, PhaseShift, CNOT
Rotational Gates	None

Purpose

Analyze diagnostic information extracted purely from quantum correlations.

3️⃣ Full Variational Quantum Circuit

Configuration

Parameter	Value
Qubits	4
Gates	RX, RY, RZ + CNOT
Variational Layers	2

Purpose

Provide maximum quantum expressibility through parameterized circuits.

⚡ Quantum Noise Robustness Study

To simulate realistic quantum hardware, the models are evaluated under four noise channels.

Noise Channel	Description
Depolarizing	Random Pauli errors
Bit Flip	Qubit state inversion
Phase Flip	Phase inversion
Amplitude Damping	Energy decay

Noise levels tested:

p = 0.01
p = 0.05
p = 0.10

This evaluates the viability of the system on NISQ (Noisy Intermediate-Scale Quantum) devices.
